# Real deploys go through the Vercel<->GitHub integration (builds from the
# repo, which never contains the paths below). This file only guards the
# `vercel` CLI / `vercel build`: without it the CLI uploads the whole working
# dir and dies on the per-file 100 MB limit (data dumps, the torch venv, the
# dev .next cache). Keep in sync with .gitignore's heavy entries.

.git
.next
node_modules
.vercel

# Multi-hundred-MB local-only artefacts, never needed for the build:
data
scripts/embeddings/.venv

# Bulk SQL dumps / backups
*.sql
*.sql.gz
